## AI Agent

This project uses two purpose-built AI agents, both implemented in `Code.gs` via Google Apps Script, calling an external LLM API for reasoning.

### Agent 1 â€” Multilingual Stock Parser (`parseRawInput`)
Takes unstructured, free-text messages in any language (Hindi, Hinglish, Kannada, English) from the `RawInput` sheet and extracts structured fields: centre name, medicine, quantity, urgency, and detected language. The result is written automatically into `StockLogs`.

### Agent 2 â€” Stock-Risk Analyzer & Redistribution Recommender (`runStockAnalysis`)
Reads current stock levels across every centre in the district, reasons about which medicines are at risk of running out relative to their threshold, checks whether any other centre has surplus of the same medicine, and writes ranked, actionable recommendations into `Alerts` â€” not just a warning, but a specific redistribution suggestion.

Both agents share a single `callAI()` function that handles the API request, so the underlying model can be swapped without touching the rest of the codebase.

