### How to Set This Up Yourself (for judges / reviewers)

You don't need our API key or Sheet access to verify this works â€” you can wire it up independently in about 10 minutes:

**1. Get your own free API key**
This project calls an OpenAI-compatible chat completions endpoint. Any compatible provider works (we used Groq's hosted Llama 3.3 70B for speed and a genuinely free tier with no card required â€” get a key at [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com)).

**2. Create your own copy of the Sheet**
- Create a new Google Sheet
- Add 4 tabs: `Centres`, `StockLogs`, `Alerts`, `RawInput`
- Column headers for each are listed in `schema.md` in this repo

**3. Add the code**
- Open **Extensions > Apps Script** from inside your Sheet
- Paste the contents of `Code.gs` from this repo

**4. Add your API key securely**
- In the Apps Script editor, click the **gear icon (Project Settings)**
- Scroll to **Script Properties > Add script property**
- Key: `AI_API_KEY`, Value: your API key
- This keeps the key out of the source code entirely â€” never hardcode it in `Code.gs`

**5. Seed sample data**
- Add a row to `Centres` (e.g., `C1, PHC Test, PHC, ..., TRUE`)
- Add a row to `RawInput` with a free-text message like:
  `Kanakapura PHC mein paracetamol bahut kam hai, sirf 5 bache hain`

**6. Run it**
- In Apps Script, select `parseRawInput` from the function dropdown, click **Run**
- Approve the permissions prompt (first run only)
- Check `StockLogs` â€” a new AI-parsed row should appear
- Add a few more stock rows, then run `runStockAnalysis`
- Check `Alerts` â€” ranked risk recommendations should appear

That's the entire agent, fully reproducible outside our environment.
